p.coef=round(coef(m)[2,], digits=3)
m.names =m$coefnames
 
s.eq=paste(s.coef[1])
p.eq=paste( p.coef[1])

for (i in 2:length(m.names)){
  s.eq=ifelse(s.coef[i]>=0, 
         paste(s.eq, "+", s.coef[i], "*", m.names[i]), 
         paste(s.eq, s.coef[i], "*", m.names[i]) 
  )}

for (i in 2:length(m.names)){
  p.eq=ifelse(p.coef[i]>=0, 
         paste(p.eq, "+", p.coef[i], "*", m.names[i]), 
         paste(p.eq, p.coef[i], "*", m.names[i]) 
  )}

#Results

#Aggregating results from models
Accuracy=c(m.mat$overall[["Accuracy"]], pca.mat$overall[["Accuracy"]], knn.mat$overall[["Accuracy"]], tr.mat$overall[["Accuracy"]], rf.mat$overall[["Accuracy"]], bag.mat$overall[["Accuracy"]], nn.mat$overall[["Accuracy"]])

Kappa=c(m.mat$overall[["Kappa"]], pca.mat$overall[["Kappa"]], knn.mat$overall[["Kappa"]], tr.mat$overall[["Kappa"]], rf.mat$overall[["Kappa"]], bag.mat$overall[["Kappa"]], nn.mat$overall[["Kappa"]])

Models=c("Multinomial", "PCA Multinom", "KNN", "Tree", "Random Forest", "Bagging", "Neural Net") 
test_res=data.frame(Models,Accuracy, Kappa)


library(reshape)
#PLotting Model test metrics
d=melt(test_res, id="Models")
colnames(d)[2]="Measurement"

ggplot(d,                                 
       aes(x = Measurement,
           y = value,
           fill = Models)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity",
           position = "dodge")+
  ggtitle("Models test metrics")

#Plotting computation costs
dcost=data.frame(Models, computational_cost=t)
ggplot(dcost,                                 
       aes(y = Models,
           x = computational_cost,
           fill = Models)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity",
           position = "dodge")+
  ggtitle("Computational Cost (in seconds)")

results=data.frame(test_res, computation_time=dcost[,2])
knitr::kable(results)
